		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The MySQL server which is relied upon for the forum was down for some hours this morning due to upgrades (particularly a full OS install/upgrade done remotely via serial console).
<br />
<br />In the process of upgrading we found that the primary/OS disk in the MySQL server is experiencing issues with its cache or circuitry on the PCA, causing some ATA I/O transactions to take up to 20 seconds to complete.  Not good.
<br />
<br />We'll be bringing the server back down again shortly (probably within the next hour) to have that disk replaced.
<br />
<br />Sorry for any inconveniences/annoyances this causes.

		

